Angola to Build 2 Million Ton a Year Cement Plant, Angop Says

-- B y   C a n d i d o   M e n d e s
-- 
2011-03-29T11:42:12Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-29/angola-to-build-2-million-ton-a-year-cement-plant-angop-says.html
Nova Cimangola,  Angola ’s biggest
cement maker, plans to build a factory to produce as much as 2
million metric tons of the building material a year,  Agencia
Angola Press  reported.  The plant will be built in the capital, Luanda, and should
start production within two years, the  news agency  said, citing
Manuel Pacavira Junior, the company’s project leader.  The southern African nation currently imports most of its
cement from China, the Luanda-based news agency said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Candido Mendes in Luanda via Johannesburg at 
 pmrichardson@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin in Johannesburg at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net  